article.description: Kelsey Bolte scored 23 points and Alison Lacey added 20 as Iowa State (No. 24 ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) beat Colorado 76-63 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Bolte, Lacey power Cyclones past Buffs
article.linkText: No. 24 Iowa State holds off upstart Colorado
article.story:
AMES, Iowa -- Kelsey Bolte scored 23 points and Alison Lacey added 20 as Iowa State (No. 24 ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) beat Colorado 76-63 on Wednesday night.

Nicky Wieben also had 19 points for the Cyclones (20-7, 8-5 Big 12), who used a 24-5 advantage from the foul line to secure the win.

Kara Richards had 21 points and 10 rebounds and Kelly Jo Mullaney added 20 points for Colorado (11-14, 3-10).

Iowa State was 24-for-26 from the line with Lacey going 10-for-10. Colorado made five of seven free throws.

Bolte made five of the Cyclones' 10 3-pointers and grabbed nine rebounds.

The Buffaloes led by one early in the game, but Iowa State took a 36-31 lead at the break and extended it to as many as 23 points late in the game.
